The 52-year-old man and his wife were attacked by a group of men while they were sleeping on Thursday night. Police are investigating. CAPE TOWN - A Port Elizabeth man has been hospitalised following an attack at his home in Sea View.The 52-year-old man and his wife were attacked by a group of men while they were sleeping Thursday night.The intruders were armed with an axe and screwdrivers.The police's Sandra Janse van Rensburg says the man was stabbed numerous times. Three suspects entered the property and attacked the man. The wife was also injured and she was taken to hospital for medical treatment. We re investigating a case of house robbery. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)